'''Fatty acid photodecarboxylase''' is an enzyme that converts fatty acids to [[alkanes]] or [[alkenes]], which can then, in principle, be used as [[biofuel]].  The enzyme has been found in ''[[Chlorella variabilis]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/51391/title/A-Newly-Identified-Photoenzyme-Helps-Algae-Pump-Out-Fuel/|title=A Newly Identified Photoenzyme Helps Algae Pump Out Fuel|last=Zimmer|first=Katarina|date=2018-02-01|website=The Scientist|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

